[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scottish Cup: Raith Rovers v Hearts to be shown live by BBC Scotland

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
BBC Scotland will broadcast live coverage of Raith Rovers v Heart of Midlothian in the fourth round of the Scottish Cup.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The game will be shown by Sportscene on BBC One Scotland, with a 13:05 GMT kick-off on Sunday, 22 January.
The action will be shown on the BBC Sport website, with BBC Radio Scotland also providing commentary.
The teams last met in season 2015-15, with Hearts winning all four meetings in the Championship.
The Stark's Park hosts are managed by Gary Locke, a former boss and player with the visitors, while Rudi Skacel, Jason Thomson and Kevin McHattie are ex-Hearts players in the home ranks.
Hearts won the Scottish Cup for the eighth time in 2012, while Rovers have been in one final, losing to Falkirk in 1913.
